author: Salim Essaid
text:
Wonderful staff and friendly local gym.

Other gyms are overpriced, charging up to SG $60 for one time gym use. Anytime Fitness allowed me to use the well equipped gym, their hospitality was a highlight of my trip. Come here if travelling, and also living here.

author: Vidya Kothari
text: Honestly paying a membership for unclean equipment and toilets is a bit much. There is no upkeep of cleanliness with toilets full of flies and stains of others fluids, even cockroaches. and it has been the same for days, maybe even weeks. I come every morning to the same level of cleanliness; it's a bit much. Please do something about it, if not, what's the point of paying compared to a local, cheaper gym?

author: Daniel Ng
text:
A strange AF located right opposite Cantonment Police Station. It's a 4-storey shop house. The 1st level kinda has dungeon vibes, very gritty, low ceilings, 1 squat rack, smith machine, leg press, deadlift platform and dumbbells up to 50kg. L2 has cardio machines and a couple of random plate loaded machines. L3 is all Life Fitness machines with the cable stack as well. At L4 there's a random glute extension and back extension as well as dual pulley cables. Overall it's a little bit small and narrow but decently well equipped. The showers are very tiny though and aren't exactly the cleanest around. Overall a convenient gym if you're in the area but loses a couple stars due to cleanliness/maintenance and inconvenience of the 4-floor layout.

Not ideal for leg day cos you'll have to climb stairs haha.

author: Tarcisus Ho
text:
Been here on two occasions. Once on a Saturday evening and another on a Monday evening. It gets crowded on weekdays evening but it‚Äôs really quiet on weekends.

I do not usually patronise the gym but it is a nice experience to gym in a shop house. The gym has four floors and the toilets/shower is located at the end of each floor except the top floor. Equipment is new and in good condition.

author: Pinyan Gao
text:
The gym manager blocked my access card and has ghosted my emails after already resolving the membership issue

In addition, the bathrooms are not hygienic and the staff are always heating up and eating food in the weights area which is unpleasant to see/smell

author: Bear Melon
text:
CBD area and near from MRT
Unique shop house building
Variation of machine( Decline press etc )
Not new , but good maitaned

divided 4 floor , not easy to move
Few racks , not enough free weight space
Limited shower(small and tired)
SO Bad attitude 2Personal trainers

Good for breast ,arm,shoulder training

author: Chili Red Arowana
text: Nice outlet, but the cycle machine abit old have some weird squeaky noise every time I paddle. Toilet shower you have to switch on the heater button is outside the toilet‚Ä¶ if you forgot and already naked inside you will have to shower in cold water‚Ä¶ overall nice outlet, 6-8pm not too crowded

author: Aless Leong
text:
The gym underwent Renovation and the lightning and mood feels like a hotel stay. Though the ambience is calm but it makes you sleepy and no motivation to gym. Equipments are still the same and some dumbbells are stained with white paint? Toilets are the same as before, no deep cleaning either.
Only plus point is when cooling down at level 4 you can feel zen and peaceful as it sets the mood (minus the gym music, doubt it‚Äôs even Spotify, horrible taste in music)

author: Andy Low
text: Well equipped and clean gym! Friendly staff and members over there made the weight lifting experience great. The equipments there are great for beginners who doesn't know how to activate certain muscle group. Kudos to the owner for getting equipment that other anytime fitness doesn't have

author: David (Bingobob)
text:
A well equipped gym with a wide range of equipment suitable for all type of workouts whether it be circuit training, resistance training, cardio  or even yoga, there is space and equipment for you.
The team are a friendly bunch of people, always smiling and happy to see you, and are very generous with tips and tricks to get the best out of your work out if you ask.

author: Yully Yyyy
text: Anytime Fitness Cantonment is seriously the best. Not only is it large and spacious, the toilet smells nice compared to other AF branches which I appreciate a lot. The weights are always kept and things are always packed neatly and organized. You'll be spoiled coming to this AF and would not want to go anywhere else. (+ the people here are nice)

author: TRaV N
text:
Well equipped and neat! With a wide range of knowledgable trainers.

An entire private level with huge mirrors for classes and functional training.

The most unique anytime fitness in Singapore situated inside a conservation shophouse.

Don't be fooled from the outside..it is relatively big inside with 4 different levels!

author: Noh Danial
text: Conveniently located near the mrt. Just 1-2mins walk away from the station exit. Equipment are well maintained and has many levels. Love the spacious open area (dedicated level) for rope work and various functional trainings. Toilet is also very clean and maintained.

author: san chua
text:
Very near MRT station hence it‚Äôs very convenient.
Equipment is not very new but it‚Äôs fine, staffs are friendly.
But cleanliness definitely not the best compare to other gym I have been to

author: lukman umar
text: Awesome place to workout. Trainers and staff are knowleageable, friendly and willing to assist at all times. Gym equipment and free weights are great. Good place to come if your aim is to build muscle.

author: Nithi Tangsirisap
text: Surprisingly quite quiet in the morning of weekdays. Not so crowded on weekends during the days as well. It's quite an experience going to a gym in a shop house like this one. I'm impressed how they manage to squeeze all these equipments in such a tiny space quite efficiently.

author: Alan Hsu
text: Very small space to the point it becomes somewhat unsafe, 4 floors means difficult to superset or giant set between barbells and machines. Bells are dusty and no alcohol wipes or sprays. I visited between 3-4:30pm on a Tuesday afternoon, only a few people but some were eating on the machines while talking very loudly, prob due to the very small space. Recommend Tiong Bahru or even queensway is better than this branch.

author: ayam kampung
text:
Equipments are new and clean. But the gym itself is small and packed. Been visiting during the supposedly ‚Äúoff peak‚Äù hour but still got too many ppl especially at the free weight area. It can also get so hot inside, as only one third of air cons r turned on
NB. half of the machines cant be used due to safe distancing measure.

author: Kimberly Dickson
text: Great gym and facilities, terrible taste in music. Tuneless hard style and eurotrash blasts throughout the place. If you want music induced anxiety, this is the gym for you.

author: Jasmine B
text:
Best AF I have visited so far with really nice space and facilities. Staffs and PTs like are extremely knowledgeable and friendly, always available to help.
Spanning across 4 levels also means that not everything is cramped together, allow walking space and a little private ‚Äúme time‚Äù at different machines.
Will always return for my weekly workout, good job AF Cantonment!

author: Wei Chan
text: Gym equipment is comprehensive, clean and well maintained and it is not over crowded. Conveniently located right next to Outram MRT. Affordable membership prices as well. Highly recommend

author: K Daron
text:
It's a great gym that has a total of 4 levels.

Basement level is where most of the strength equipments are at and they have a single power rack and a deadlift platform. Dumbbells ranges from 1kg-50kg.

First level has cardio machines and some hammer strength machines.

Second level has most of the life fitness machines. They also have the multi-jungle equipment.

Top level has another jungle equipment set. There is also another cable machine with lots of cardio equipments (Rope, TRX, abs roller, box, etc)

Overall I'll rate it as a good gym. It is usually not that crowded but when it does, it may be quite troublesome because theres only one power rack.

author: Christopher Bobin
text: I've gone to a number of AnyTime Fitness outlets in Singapore: this one works for me and is one of the best in my opinion.  Four floors in a shophouse provides decent scale and a wide range of equipment.  Staff is courteous and not intrusive.  There are trainers available if that's what you require; otherwise, they leave you alone. A nice mix of local and expat clients, centrally located near the Outram MRT station gives it a nice vibe.

author: Jaycee LS
text:
This isn't as great as what others says on their review.

Pros:
4 levels of space.
Number of equipments.

Cons:
RUDE AND HOSTILE STAFFS.
Dark.
Whining PTs and members.
Rusty bars.
Feels like maze.
Members bang and drops heavy equipment resulting to shaky floor.
Staff, PTs, and members eat food in the equipment.

Recommendations:
Better go to other branches like Tanjong Pagar or Keppel where equipments are better and brighter.

author: Lina Kim
text: The hygiene of this gym is absolutely disgusting! This is where my membership money goes?! Y‚Äôall don‚Äôt even care to maintain the cleanliness. Not the first time I see this, but I‚Äôm absolutely fed up with this.

author: Adam Chan
text: Friendly trainers, ample racks & machines to work out with. Convienently located next to MRT. Toilets & overall cleanliness can be improved.

author: oil all
text: Gym Manger, the older guy with white hair is very rude

author: Ida Einjaw
text: Small area but 4 levels and fully equipped. Can be awkward and claustrophobic if crowded.

author: Jon
text: Cramped, small, squeezy. Have to climb stairs every time to find the right machine for every part of workout. One of the smallest AFs around

author: Ryan Davis Ng
text: Absolutely awful feel to this club. As other reviews say‚Ä¶a hostile feel. Once you‚Äôre tied down to a contract and the money is in the bag, they don‚Äôt reply to your emails. No compassion and just hungry for money.  1*

author: Lynn C
text: " An eye for detail for form correction and excellent cue skills is what make Kenneth differentiate from other personal trainers. Highly recommended if you are committed to your fitness journey!"

author: Nick Wong
text: Great place to workout. Friendly team of trainers and staff to guide and train you! Can't beat 4 levels of gym equipment and fitness space!!

author: Tiger Magno
text: Clean and spacious gym!

author: Repsaj Eel
text: Unique layout compared to other gyms. Equipment well maintained

author: Zaki Khan
text: Cosy gym. Placed in a warehouse and becsuse of that there are different levels. Each storey has its own offerings eg. Cardio, weightlifting. Good place for a quiet workout

author: Jeremy Lim
text: Cosy gym, could use more free weights.

author: Rahul Baid
text: For an AF gym, one of the better ones. Due to multiple storeys, you get free cardio

author: Ben Soon
text: Love it...Nice gym. The staff there so friendly and helpful.

author: DEN15
text: Revised operating hours and both weekdays and weekends unlike some other branches. Weekdays 8am to 11pm. Weekends 9am to 5pm. Due to social distancing measure some of the equipments are "tagged out" and not to be used.

author: christy lim
text: Amazing gym & adequate equipments for a good workout!

text: Best place.. organised gym with nice ambiance friendly staff..

text: A clean and complete gym. Though it's often very crowded at night

author: richard lim
text: Nice place to work out. Staffs are friendly and helpful.

author: Grace Teo
text: Love the layout! Friendly staffs! :)
